   "source": [
    "# chemhist â€” Installation and Usage Example\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates how to install and use the `chemhist` package to generate histogram-based descriptors from chemical formulas."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3c8abf7c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Installation\n",
    "\n",
    "```bash\n",
    "pip install chemhist\n",
    "```\n",
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "9efa9745",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#!pip install .\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5ad40b28",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Generate Histogram Descriptors\n",
    "Use `get_descriptor` to convert a chemical formula into a numerical histogram vector."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "7737d610",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from chemhist import get_descriptor\n",
    "\n",
    "formula = 'Li0.5Mn1.0O2'\n",
    "vec, labels = get_descriptor(formula, algebricdesc=True, matrixdesc=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Descriptor vector length:', len(vec))\n",
    "print('First 10 values:', vec[:10])\n",
    "print('First 10 labels:', labels[:10])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1d676c9d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Visualize the Descriptor\n",
    "Display the descriptor as a histogram."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "3ac25ed5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 4))\n",
    "plt.bar(range(len(vec)), vec, color='steelblue')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Descriptor Index')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Value')\n",
    "plt.title(f'Histogram Descriptor for {formula}')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "49458d61",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Grouped Visualization by Property\n",
    "Plot the descriptor grouped by property name (EN, AN, IR, etc.), preserving the original order of appearance."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "dfc02c48",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "props = [l.split('_')[0] for l in labels]\n",
    "unique_props = []\n",
    "for p in props:\n",
    "    if p not in unique_props:\n",
    "        unique_props.append(p)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 4))\n",
    "for p in unique_props:\n",
    "    idx = [i for i, l in enumerate(labels) if l.startswith(p)]\n",
    "    plt.bar(idx, vec[idx], label=p)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.legend(unique_props, ncol=4)\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Descriptor Index (in original order)')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Value')\n",
    "plt.title(f'Histogram Descriptors Grouped by Property ({formula})')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a2c76c2b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Save Descriptor to CSV\n",
    "Export the computed descriptor vector and labels to a CSV file."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "7e9a85c9",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "df = pd.DataFrame([vec], columns=labels)\n",
    "df.insert(0, 'formula', formula)\n",
    "df.to_csv('chemhist_output.csv', index=False)\n",
    "print('Saved as chemhist_output.csv')"
   ]
  }
 ],
